= El enlace con la montaña

*Aplica a ambos caminos. En la vía política, es su contacto tenue y deniable con los que subieron a la sierra; en la vía armada, es quien le lleva la guerra a la ciudad y le trae la ciudad a la guerra.*

You never learn the real name, and you make a point of not trying. The contact arrives at safe kitchens by routes that change every time, carries nothing written, and speaks of the compañeros in the sierra the way one speaks of relatives in a country at war — with love, and with the specific exhaustion of someone who buries them. This is the thread that runs under the whole Movement whether you admit it or not: the deniable link between the left that signs its name and the left that cannot. In the years of the dirty war it is the most dangerous relationship you have, and, some months, the most useful.

